A livestock recovery mission at the sprawling Embobut Forest on the border of Elgeyo Marakwet and West Pokot counties turned awry when a police officer was killed in an ambush by armed cattle raiders. The Administration Police (AP) officer attached to Kamelei Anti-Stock Theft Unit was shot in the head on Friday morning when the raiders opened fire on the security personnel at Kamologon in the dense forest. ALSO READ:

Man killed as he fights off rapists An unconfirmed number of raiders were killed in the shootout, with the security officers managing to recover an AK47 assault rifle with 16 bullets. KFS Embobut commander David Rono said other officers ducked to safety.